dcterms:creator: Warwick Tucker
dcterms:description: The Lorenz attractor is a set of chaotic solutions of the Lorenz system, which is a system of ordinary differential equations originally developed to model atmospheric convection.
dcterms:title: Lorenz Attractor

dcterms:creator: Christophe Letellier
Otto E. Rossler
dcterms:description: The Rossler attractor is a system of three non-linear ordinary differential equations that exhibits chaotic behavior, often used in the study of dynamical systems.
dcterms:title: Rossler Attractor
